Their ordeal caused a wave of solidarity and anti-Iran feelings in home.
The Iran crisis significantly influenced Jimmy Carter's loss with Ronald Reagan in 1980 presidential elections.
The film Argo, directed by Ben Affleck, recounts one episode in this story, which brought America a small victory.
After the embassy was seized, six employees escaped.
After some peripheral situations, they ended in the Canadian ambassador's home.
The CIA, in collaboration with Canada, managed to get them out of Iran, thanks to an extravagant cover story - they left on Canadian passports as members of a film crew, surveying locations for a sci-fi blockbuster.
A combination of genres
