On the other hand, there is a realistic political thriller, and at the same time a "caper movie" with small victories and double crossing - another example would be Ocean's Eleven.
The mood varies in the film - on one side, sharp documentary-style sequences in Tehran (the title sequence shows iconic photos from the time, relating to the same events portrayed in the film - no major differences).
