Spijkenisse, a quiet town outside Rotterdam, which does not merit a visit, is a special record-holder.
The 80,000-resident municipality has the lowest literacy rate in the Netherlands.
In order to counteract this almost alike situation, the decision was made many years ago to recreate the seven fictitious bridges that feature on the Euro notes as painted reinforced concrete miniatures.
The success of the education offensive was limited.
The city fathers recognized that there is only one way to become master of statistics: a library had to be built!
Winy Maas of MVRDV, a leading architect in Rotterdam, took the project with his usual composure, and turned up at the competitive hearing in 2003 with five books under his arm and a smile on his face.
